//dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"disgrace\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 157}, {\"ngram\": \"its creators\", \"from\": 165, \"to\": 177}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"a show\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very open-minded but I thought what they did was a disgrace,\\\" Trump told Fox News.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4005773968266686e-17, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a disgrace\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 303}, {\"ngram\": \"Trump\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 311}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked by host Laura Ingraham what he would do if he's reelected President in time for the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles, Trump replied: \\\"We will not be having a 'Last Supper' as portrayed the way they portrayed it.\\\"\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 347, \"end\": 361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Ingraham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.529615435317536e-21, \"text\": \"Laura Ingraham\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Ingraham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Ingraham\"}, {\"begin\": 440, \"end\": 451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999999879492, \"rank\": 6.4182454604027064e-12, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 453, \"end\": 458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999657399526233, \"rank\": 3.426121891387334e-05, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"President\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 406}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 414}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympics\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'Last Supper\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"unintentional parody\\\" of the Last Supper angered Christians and Catholics.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 604, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6482872938739149, \"rank\": 0.46764557616373426, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998865405, \"rank\": 1.1050802788371463e-10, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The \\\"unintentional parody\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The outrage sparked after the ceremony featured a scene reminiscent of da Vinci's painting with a transgender model, drag queens, and a man in a very revealing outfit.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The outrage\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 642}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 669}, {\"ngram\": \"a scene\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 686}, {\"ngram\": \"da Vinci's painting\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"a transgender model\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"a very revealing outfit\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers now claim the unintentionalparody of the Last Supper was meant to represent Dionysusand raise awareness of the absurdity of violence among humans.\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organizers\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"the unintentionalparody\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 844}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"Dionysusand\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 898}, {\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 931}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 943}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"InGreek mythology,Dionysusis the god of wine, vegetation, fertility, festivity, ritual madness, religious ecstasy, and theater.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"InGreek mythology\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"Dionysusis\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 987}, {\"ngram\": \"the god\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 995}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"vegetation\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1015}, {\"ngram\": \"fertility\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1026}, {\"ngram\": \"festivity\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"ritual madness\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"religious ecstasy\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1072}, {\"ngram\": \"theater\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to myth, Dionysus was born twice.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.528919129292313e-18, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"myth\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sketch drew condemnation from Catholic groups and French bishops.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1166, \"end\": 1174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999958262859097, \"rank\": 4.093396581056628e-06, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9388237208229001, \"rank\": 0.059372393051017956, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sketch\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1142}, {\"ngram\": \"condemnation\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1160}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were joined by the Head of the Orthodox Church,Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"score\": 0.8917980435632861, \"rank\": 0.07478570616283273, \"text\": \"Orthodox\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Orthodox_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Head\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement released by the Patriarchate in Constantinople, Bartholomew expressed his \\\"deepest sadness\\\" for the blasphemy of God.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1352, \"end\": 1363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bartholomew_I_of_Constantinople\", \"score\": 0.9999999967174062, \"rank\": 3.282690174394792e-09, \"text\": \"Bartholomew\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bartholomew_I_of_Constantinople\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bartholomew_I_of_Constantinople\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"the Patriarchate\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"Constantinople\", \"from\": 1336, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"his \\\"deepest sadness\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1394}, {\"ngram\": \"the blasphemy\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was with great sadness that we watched during the ceremony in Paris offensive performances for Christianity and the holy Gospel, but also for every civilized person, who recognizes the right to believe and respect religious symbols,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999997766333558, \"rank\": 2.2336658481984358e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8096763188768608, \"rank\": 0.23506112396605444, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"holy Gospel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gospel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"great sadness\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"offensive performances\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"every civilized person\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1591}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 1608, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"religious symbols\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"These images not only did not brighten the ceremony, but tarnished it.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These images\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is not progress to blaspheme God, nor is it a right to insult the religious beliefs of our fellow human beings.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"progress\", \"from\": 1753, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1778}, {\"ngram\": \"a right\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"the religious beliefs\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"our fellow human beings\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The spontaneous expression of disgust and disapproval on the part of the world, we hope, has sent a sufficiently loud message to the decision-makers and is a source of hope for avoiding similar actions in the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 2077, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The spontaneous expression\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"disgust\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1897}, {\"ngram\": \"disapproval\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1913}, {\"ngram\": \"the part\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"a sufficiently loud message\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1985}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision-makers\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2008}, {\"ngram\": \"a source\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2024}, {\"ngram\": \"hope\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2032}, {\"ngram\": \"similar actions\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2061}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2075}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pressure generated by the sketch in theopening ceremonyprompted a press conference from the Paris 2024 organizers.\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2175, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.309600266649604e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The pressure\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"the sketch\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2115}, {\"ngram\": \"a press conference\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2165}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spokesperson Anne Descamps stated, \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an intention\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"any religious group\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The inauguration tried to celebrate community and tolerance.\\\"\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The inauguration\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"community\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2360}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, she added, \\\"We believe this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this ambition\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2494, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2442, \"to\": 2448}, {\"ngram\": \"any offense\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to Descamps's comments, the director of the Last Supper scene at the Olympics, Thomas Jolly, said that religious criticism was not his intention.\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}, {\"begin\": 2587, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9999996510740101, \"rank\": 3.021510540658707e-07, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2507}, {\"ngram\": \"the director\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2544}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper scene\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2585}, {\"ngram\": \"religious criticism\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2630}, {\"ngram\": \"his intention\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In his defense, Jolly insisted, \\\"We wanted to talk about diversity.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his defense\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2669}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2676}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2721}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Diversity means being together.\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Diversity\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted to include everyone, as simple as that.\\\"\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"See all thelatest newsfrom Greece and the world atGreekreporter.com.Contact our newsroomto report an update or send your story, photos and videos.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2834, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9800838339832953, \"rank\": 0.020320586042231855, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world atGreekreporter.com\", \"from\": 2845, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"Contact\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"our newsroomto\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2897}, {\"ngram\": \"an update\", \"from\": 2905, \"to\": 2914}, {\"ngram\": \"your story\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"photos\", \"from\": 2935, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 2946, \"to\": 2952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow GR onGoogle Newsandsubscribe hereto our daily email!\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow GR onGoogle Newsandsubscribe\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2989}, {\"ngram\": \"our daily email\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3012}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 Copyright - GreekReporter.com\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00a9 Copyright - GreekReporter.com\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3046}]}]}"